<ttl id="1000Y_S0016_72ZS3_T00CJ" variety="T00CJ">
<name>AIRBAG SYSTEM</name>
<para id="RM000000XFH00SX" category="U" type-id="303FJ" name-id="RS2D0-01" from="200601">
<name>DATA LIST / ACTIVE TEST</name>
<subpara id="RM000000XFH00SX_z0" proc-id="RM0250U___000072500000">
<content5 releasenbr="1">
<atten4>
<ptxt>By accessing the DATA LIST displayed on the intelligent tester, you can perform such functions as reading the values of switches and sensors without removing any parts. Reading the DATA LIST as the first step in troubleshooting is one method to save labor time.</ptxt>
</atten4>
<step1>
<ptxt>DATA LIST FOR CENTER AIRBAG SENSOR ASSEMBLY</ptxt>
<step2>
<ptxt>Connect the intelligent tester to the DLC3.</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="C131977E01" width="2.775699831in" height="2.775699831in"/>
</figure>
</step2>
<step2>
<ptxt>Turn the ignition switch on (IG).</ptxt>
</step2>
<step2>
<ptxt>Turn the tester ON.</ptxt>
</step2>
<step2>
<ptxt>Enter the following menus: DIAGNOSIS / OBD/MOBD / SRS AIRBAG / DATA LIST.</ptxt>
</step2>
<step2>
<ptxt>Check the values by referring to the table below.</ptxt>
<table pgwide="1">
<title>DATA LIST</title>
<tgroup cols="4">
<colspec colname="COL1" colwidth="1.77in"/>
<colspec colname="COL2" colwidth="1.77in"/>
<colspec colname="COL3" colwidth="1.77in"/>
<colspec colname="COL4" colwidth="1.77in"/>
